reviews.review_text: Laurie is awesome. She helped me a lot and patiently. Definitely I will come back here.
All staff Respectful, time committed, and arranged i love this pharmacy
Good

The service took almost 1 hour but its perfect time do your errands at Superstore. I had so much time to shop around. When I was done shopping for 1 hour, I came back to pick up the prescription. I had to wait a few more minutes but it was still perfect timing.

This pharmacy is good but only thing is long and slow lines is negative point of this pharmacy, flu shot always available with professional pharmacist with smiley face make you feeling better, this store located inside the superstore and wheelchair access is very easy and location is near to public transits such as sky train or bus

Superstore is my shopping store. Each store is very different. the superstoer on grandview is clean and tidy.  Staff greeting you or saying have a good day is very rare.  the  self check out is where i rely on staff saying thankyou and have a good day. i get nothing and there are times there are2 people talking and not even paying attention to customers.   Cashiers are more friendlier  than any other staff i see working. if saying hi and have a good day is too painful for you than quit your job and stay home

Staff are polite but very slow. Pharmacy opens at 9am... don t expect them to be ready for you until 9:30. Never encountered an establishment that literally just turns on their computers for their opening hour... they should be ready to serve customers at 9am, not just getting organized for the day, come 10 minutes early and have that done and ready to go!
Staff are polite but super slow.  She say wait 30 mins.  Wait.  He say another 30 mins.  Wait.  It take 1 hour 45 mins to pick up.  Well, it is better than last time 4 hours wait.
Not sure if they care but very unfriendly in my experience . (Cody is great though).
Staff are LOVELY..BUT!!!!  Most Slowe Frustating Pharmacy iv ever been in....Staff AMAZING
Super slow service at this pharmacy, with less then friendly pharmacists working.

Un caring about the health of those filling prescriptions here, and not sure how capable the pharmacist is if they don t know what they re providing.  Refused to put items through insurance claiming they did not have a prescription. This was parts of a larger order and when asked, from the Dr. Providing the prescription, they indicated it was obvious the patient had enough information on the original prescription to process such a request and that they never heard of itemizing a prescription in this manner.  Wanted to send a vulnerable individual to walk in clinics to wait with other sick people for hours when pharmacies can prescribe themselves for clear low level issues such as this.  Also filled the rest of the prescription with other drugs know and clearly indicated to treat same issue.  Either, they do not give any care to the overall health of a person, or they don t know what they re prescribed drugs do.  Went somewhere else and was able to easily get this corrected.

What is the point of my doctor calling in HOURS ahead of time for my prescription for them to tell me to come back in TWO DAYS?!?! Are you kidding me???? Its ridiculous. Im in pain and I need my prescription immediately and you havent been able to fill the prescription within 5 flipping hours??? Is that a joke?! Who is running this place???
Never answer the phone, dont go this pharmacy. It took 2 days for picking up my medicine. They insisted they didnt get my prescription. And next day, they prepared.

I ve been on the phone for 15 minutes now trying to get through to the pharmacy for my prescription. It s just ringing and ringing. This is the second time I ve called and the same thing happened last time until finally someone answered. Also trying to pickup a prescription is a nightmare as they always take 45+ minutes. So incredibly slow. I ll be switching my prescription to a different pharmacy. I have no tolerance  for  horrendous service. Avoid this pharmacy at all costs. Absolutely horrible.

I have same prescription for over 3 years and there was no single time without an issue when I came to pick it up. The worst customer service I ever experienced especially from the older lady with long gray hair. She was very rude and unprofessional. One time she gave me my usual prescription in a half size smaller box and charging me full price. I tried to explain her that this is not correct and she wasnt even able to listen to me. I went home garbed my old box with my old receipt and went back to prove it. She wasnt there and someone else who helped me found out that second half of my prescription was forgotten to give me. If she was able to listen this would never happen. Most common issue I have when I come to pick it up, it is not ready even though I gave them few extra days. When I come they act like I have ever placed the order and they dont have it in record and they have to order something and start over. If it happened once, OK but it happens every time for over 3 years. How is that even possible? When I told her what had happen to me last time, he kept saying NO, like she could change what already happened and is not able to listen at all. Yes people have bad days but I think she hates her job and her life. I am changing the pharmacy because this service is not going  to change. If her boss was her customer she would be fired in a minute. There are overall issues with the logistics of the pharmacy but her attitude is makes everything even worst.
I call, and call, and call at different times of the day. No one answers the phone  Then you forced to go to the pharmacy and no one wants to help you. This is every time I come here. Bad service

Absolutely horrendous service. Theyre extremely slow and downright unhelpful. The pharmacist was answering a phone call while making me wait even though Id already waited 40+ mins. Id give them a zero if I could.

If I could give this pharmacy a 0 star rating I would. The pace these individuals work at is absurdly slow. There are times they serve 1 customer in 30 minutes...for no reason. No complications from the client side...just super slow service. Half the time the people behind the counter seem out of their element. It shouldnt take me 30 minutes to get my medicine that has already been packaged...I just want to pay for my product...
Terrible pharmacist, terrible service. In line, waiting for 20 minutes and 3 people working in there own world. No one helping anyone. Saw the pharmacist yell at an older lady today as well.

Everytime I have come here, I have waited at least 30 mins to pickup and drop off my prescription, at different times of the day. Usually only 1 or 2 people working. They work hard but it s unfortunate the pharmacy isn t willing to hire more staff.

Complete incompetence is the nicest way I can describe this pharmacy. Absolutely horrible. Stood in front or a tech for 10 minuets without being acknowledged at all! Very Slow service and they could never get my benefits correct if their lives depended on it. If you value your time and accuracy stay Away.

I went here for two years enduring painfully slow service because it is in superstore where I shop. One person inline ahead of you with 30 minute  waits is normal here. They just have no concept of customer service. If I could give them no stars I would. Changed over to Pharma Save on Canada Way, in and out in 5 minutes my first time and that included getting an injection.

Waits are always 40+mins and they end your prescription early - not notifying you until you come back to pick it up. My 1 year prescriptions (received at the upstairs clininc) ended between 6-9months three times in a row. I even witnessed a girl coming to pick up after she said shed dropped it off about 4 hrs ago only to find that 1 - it would take 30mins and, when corrected, 2 - We dont have any stock. We can fill this for you tomorrow. Unbelievable.
Expect huge delays to get your prescriptions ready to pick up. Consider calling before you get on your way to the drugstore because it can easily take a whole day for them to get ir ready for you.

The slowest service ever . I went there at 9 am they just opened and they told me 30 mins I asked if my medication was ready when the time has passed and still they said they were working on it. So disappointed . They should hire more staff or do something about this problem . Other pharmacies have the medication ready in 15 or 20 mins.

I would give this pharmacy a 0 star. I was told 45minutes for my prescription. I ended up waiting 2 hours. Rosie is the absolute worst, she talks on the phone instead of helping the customers in store.

I phoned for advice and waited about 15 mins before answered where an annoyed sounding woman garbled something incomprehensible on the phone before hanging up. When i finally got through i very clearly stated my question. Staff were rude and spoke to me in an exasperated way and down to me like an idiot. I was told that they couldnt fill my prescription because it doesnt exist (i know it does as ive had it before) and then told my prescription was wrong and to just come in  then told to go somewhere else. I dont know how they can operate a successful business this way. I phoned at 9:20pm on monday dec 11th.
Very slow service. Staff were ignoring customer waiting in line and did not provide any explanation or direction for my medicine. When I asked them they look annoyed and were unwilling to help.
They need a whole new team. They just make their own jobs harder being so incompetent and slow.
Tried booking a vaccine today, older Asian lady was super rude and refused to book me in and said call tomorrow and hung up
The pharmacy is beyond slow!!!!!!! Little customer service or organization!
Routinely slow.  Incompetent front line staff.  Terrible customer service overall.
Terrible customer service. No welcoming attitude. They didnt give me the right numbers of pills.
Worst pharmacy most annoying pharmacist go to Walmart instead
Super slow. Tells you 1hr, ends up being 2.
One of them super stupid.
Too slow. It takes at least 45 min every time.
Very slow and disorganized.
Rude pharmacist
